{{Infobox NRHP | name = Sts. Peter and Paul Church | nrhp_type = | image = Sts Peter and Paul Church Saint Paul Island, Alaska.jpg | caption = Church in November, 2010 | location= [[St. Paul Island, Alaska]] | coordinates = {{coord|57.1209|-170.2809|region:US-AK_type:landmark|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Alaska | built = 1907 | architecture = | added = June 6, 1980 | area = less than one acre | governing_body = Private | mpsub = {{NRHP url|id=64000002|title=Russian Orthodox Church Buildings and Sites TR}} | refnum = 80000744<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2009a}}</ref> | nrhp_type2 = nhldcp | nocat = yes | designated_nrhp_type2 = June 13, 1962 | partof = [[Seal Island Historic District]] | partof_refnum = 66000156 | designated_other1 = Alaska Heritage Resources Survey | designated_other1_name = Alaska Heritage Resources Survey | designated_other1_color = #A8EDEF | designated_other1_abbr = AHRS | designated_other1_date = May 18, 1973 | designated_other1_number = XPI-003 | designated_other1_num_position = bottom }} '''Sts. Peter and Paul Church''' ({{lang-ru|Св. Петр и Пол Черч}}) is a [[Russian Orthodox church]] on [[St. Paul Island, Alaska]]. The current church, built in 1907, was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1980.<ref name=nris/> Now it is under [[Orthodox Church in America Diocese of Alaska|Diocese of Alaska]] of the [[Orthodox Church in America]]<ref>https://oca.org/parishes/oca-ak-stpspp</ref>.
A first church was built in 1779 "according to legend"; a second church was built in 1819 atop the island's tallest hill. The current church was built in 1907, and was then "one of the most ambitiously designed and effectively executed small churches of the Byzantine tradition in Alaska." Its onion domes, however, were repeatedly damaged in storms, and have been replaced.<ref name=nrhptr>{{cite web |url={{NRHP url|id=64000002}} |title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: Russian Orthodox Church Buildings and Sites Thematic Resources |author=Alfred Mongin and Father Joseph P. Kreta |date=June 14, 1979 |publisher=National Park Service}}</ref><ref name=nrhpdoc>{{cite web|url={{NRHP url|id=80000744}} |title=Saints Peter and Paul Church (AHRS SITE NO. XPI-003) |author=Alfred Mongin and Father Joseph P. Kreta |date=June 14, 1979 |publisher=National Park Service}} (continuation sheet from thematic resources document) and {{NRHP url|id=80000744|title=accompanying three photos from 1961, c.1973, and undated|photos=y}}</ref>
